         <t:abstract>
            <t:p>The <t:foreign xml:lang="gez">Fǝtḥa nagaśt</t:foreign> is a book of law which was in use in Ethiopia from the <t:date>16th century</t:date>
            and was still referenced to in the Penal and Civil Codes of <t:date>1930</t:date>, <t:date>1957</t:date> and <t:date>1960</t:date>.</t:p>
            <t:p>The date of its translation from the Arabic <t:ref target="#t2arabic"/> by <t:persName role="translator" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7834PetrosA">Ṗeṭros ʾAbda Sayd</t:persName> is debated, possibly it was translated in the <t:date>16th century</t:date>.</t:p>
            <t:p>
